# Demo Plan — 7 days (PM-led)

## Goal
Deliver a credible “product demo” that proves the end-to-end workflow and validates MVP scope with stakeholders.

## Demo story (10–12 minutes)
1. Admin creates an event (theme, banner, programme upload)
2. Admin publishes the event → it appears on the public calendar
3. External user registers → admin verifies
4. Verified user enters Deal Room → filters deals by country/sector
5. User opens a deal → requests prospectus → schedules a 1:1 meeting
6. Admin dashboard shows engagement signals (downloads, requests, meetings)
7. (Optional) Admin generates a Deal Book dataset export

## Daily sprint checklist
### Day 1 — MVP decisions
- Confirm MVP modules and out-of-scope list
- Confirm stages/statuses
- Freeze v1 data dictionary fields

### Day 2 — Wireframes
- Create low-fidelity wireframes for 8 screens
- Define navigation map

### Day 3 — Clickable prototype
- Build clickable flow (Figma or slides)
- Populate with sample data

### Day 4 — Script + acceptance criteria
- Write demo talk track
- Draft acceptance criteria per module

### Day 5 — Dev handover pack
- Finalize docs in `/docs`
- Create GitHub issues backlog

### Day 6 — Rehearsal + gap fixes
- Run demo end-to-end
- Remove clutter, tighten story

### Day 7 — Final demo assets
- Final prototype link
- Backup recording (3–5 min)
